# TalentLock — Cursor Agent Rules

## Before Every Task
- Read `project.md` first. Never assume the schema, routes, or tech stack from memory.
- Read the relevant `specs/{feature}/plan.md` before writing any code.
- Read the relevant `specs/{feature}/task.md` before writing any code.
- Read `specs/{feature}/UI.md` before writing any frontend component (Phase 3 only).
- If `plan.md` and `task.md` conflict, `plan.md` wins — always.

## Architecture Rules
- Frontend lives in `artifacts/talentlock/src/`
- Backend lives in `artifacts/api-server/src/`
- Database schema lives in `lib/db/src/schema/` — multiple files, edit the relevant one
- Always use Drizzle ORM — never write raw SQL
- After editing any schema file run: `pnpm --filter @workspace/db run push`
- API hooks are generated via Orval — import from `@workspace/api-client-react`
- Zod schemas for request validation — import from `@workspace/api-zod`
- Never hand-edit generated files in `lib/api-client-react/src/` or `lib/api-zod/src/`
- Auth is Clerk — never implement custom auth logic
- Admin auth is a separate HMAC-signed cookie (`tl_admin`) — completely independent of Clerk
- Use `req.log` (Pino) in route handlers — never `console.log`
- Vite proxies all `/api` calls to `localhost:8080` — no CORS configuration needed

## API Workflow (OpenAPI → codegen)
The single source of truth for the API contract is `lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml`.

When adding a new endpoint:
1. Add the route definition in `lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml`
2. Run `pnpm --filter @workspace/api-spec run codegen`
3. Implement the route in `artifacts/api-server/src/routes/`
4. Register it in `artifacts/api-server/src/index.ts`
5. Use the generated hook in the frontend

After every codegen run — mandatory checks:
- `lib/api-zod/orval.config.ts` must still have `indexFiles: false`
- `lib/api-zod/src/index.ts` must only export `./generated/api`
- Run `pnpm run typecheck` — fix all errors before any frontend work

## Coding Rules
- Never modify freelancer-facing pages unless the task explicitly says so
- All new API routes must be registered in `artifacts/api-server/src/index.ts`
- All quota checks must use `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` inside a Drizzle transaction
- HTTP 402 errors must return `{ error, code, planNeeded }` — match existing pattern
- Frontend 402 `TOKEN_LIMIT` handlers show inline error — do NOT redirect to /pricing
- Frontend 402 `PLAN_LIMIT` handlers redirect to /pricing — match PostJob/JobDetail pattern
- Do not use `localStorage` in React components — use `sessionStorage` or React state
- Never store AI output in form state until the employer explicitly clicks Accept

## Schema Changes Workflow
1. Edit the relevant file in `lib/db/src/schema/`
2. Run `pnpm --filter @workspace/db run push`
3. If migration affects existing data — run backfill SQL immediately after push
4. Verify columns exist in Neon before proceeding to backend work

## Spec Execution Order
Always execute tasks in this phase order:
1. Database (schema + migration + backfill if needed)
2. Backend API (utilities → routes → OpenAPI → codegen → typecheck)
3. Frontend (hooks → components → page integrations)
4. Admin console

Rules:
- Never start Phase 2 before Phase 1 migration is confirmed in Neon
- Never start Phase 3 before Phase 2 codegen is confirmed and typecheck passes
- Never start Phase 4 before Phase 3 typecheck passes
- Execute only the phase instructed — do not jump ahead

## What the Agent Reads Per Phase
| Phase | Files to read |
|---|---|
| Verification | `project.md` + `plan.md` + `task.md` |
| Phase 1 — Database | `project.md` + `plan.md` + `task.md` |
| Phase 2 — Backend | `project.md` + `plan.md` + `task.md` |
| Phase 3 — Frontend | `project.md` + `plan.md` + `task.md` + `UI.md` |
| Phase 4 — Admin | `project.md` + `plan.md` + `task.md` + `UI.md` |
| Validation | `project.md` + `validation.md` |

`features.md` and `clarify.md` are reference documents for humans — the agent does not need them during execution.

## What NOT to Do
- Do not invent file paths — use only paths specified in `task.md`
- Do not add Stripe or email logic — deferred to a future phase
- Do not add token tracking to freelancer routes
- Do not hand-write React Query hooks — always run codegen
- Do not skip the post-codegen checks (`indexFiles: false`, `index.ts` exports, typecheck)
- Do not run migrations without also running any required backfill SQL
- Do not modify the form's description state from inside an AI assistant component — use the `onAccept` callback only
- Do not redirect to `/pricing` for `TOKEN_LIMIT` errors inside drawers or inline panels — show the error inline

## Useful Commands Reference
```bash
# Install all workspace dependencies
pnpm install

# Push DB schema changes
pnpm --filter @workspace/db run push

# Regenerate API client after editing openapi.yaml
pnpm --filter @workspace/api-spec run codegen

# Type-check the entire workspace
pnpm run typecheck

# Type-check a single package
pnpm --filter @workspace/talentlock run typecheck
pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run typecheck

# Run API server in dev mode
pnpm --filter @workspace/api-server run dev

# Run frontend in dev mode
pnpm --filter @workspace/talentlock run dev

# Seed demo freelancers
pnpm --filter @workspace/scripts run seed
```
